Question 1.4.1 (Scale-Free Character of Newton's Method)

Function: x = Sy

The problem demonstrates Newton's Method with an uneffected scale and invertible direction.

A scale example, x^{k+1} = S*y^{k+1}
    
                         = S*[y^k - alpha^k*delf(y^k)/del[delf(y^k)]
  
                         = S*y^k - S*alpha^k*delf(y^k)/del[delf(y^k)]
 
                         = x^k - alpha^k*delf(x^k)/del[delf(x^k)]

An invertible example, y^{k+1} = S^-1 * x^{k+1}
 
                               = S^-1 * [x^k - alpha^k*delf(x^k)/del[delf(x^k)]

                               = S*x^k - S*alpha^k*delf(x^k)/del[delf(x^k)]

                               = y^k - alpha^k*delf(y^k)/del[delf(y^k)]

Rules: Newton's Method 
        x^{k+1} = x^k - alpha^k*delf(x^k)/del[delf(x^k)]
